Begin by Loading in all the data, and plotting a linear model with all the variables. Make sure to set your working directory. All project code/csv/excel/etc files can be found at https://github.com/Rmcortez12/stat-learning. Also do some preliminary scatter plot analysis. Were fairly certain all the relationships are linear.

library(MASS)
library(car)
## Loading required package: carData
#Load Data

setwd("d:/UTSA/Fall2020/DataMining/Project/stat-learning") # set working directory
df = read.csv('FinalDF.csv') # read in raw csv data


df$Age15_19 = as.factor(df$Age15_19)

Remove interaction effects because of high multicollinearity and small sample sets. There are less than 10 runners per team, and there are guidelines which forces individual team runners to end as a team. By including them were overfitting.

The Above is the final model all parameters are significant. Use GLM fit in order to do cross validation. During initial validation the interaction effects were kept in, and because theyre categorical the LOOCV had to be used to ensure all countries were included in each validation step. If we had done any type of training split its possible that some countries could have been excluded. Once the interaction effects were removed, the LOOCV was still kept as the validation method.

for (j in 1:10) {
  error <- c()
  for (i in 1:nrow(df.filtered.2)) {
    model <- glm(logy ~ .
                - Yards
                -Sweden
              - median_rate_q1
              - median_rate_q2
              - median_rate_q3
              - median_rate_q4
              - median_sec_q1
             - median_sec_q2
              - median_sec_q3
              - median_sec_q4
              - avg_rate_q1
              - avg_rate_q2
              - avg_rate_q3
                -Russia
              - MaxSeconds
                -Finland
                -Canada
                -Ukraine
                -Switzerland
                -Denmark
                -Belgium
                -Ireland
             - difference
                -UK
                -Germany
                -France
                -NZ
                -US
                -Japan
                -Spain
                -Australia
                -Mexico
                -India
                -Singapore
                -Belarus
                - rate_sd1
                - rate_sd2
                -rate_sd3
                -rate_sd4
                -avg_sec_q2
                -avg_sec_q1
                -sd_q2
                - avg_sec_q4
              - range_q2, data = df.filtered.2[-i,])
    prediction <- predict(model, newdata = df.filtered.2[i,])
    error[i] <- (prediction - df.filtered.2[i, "logy"]) ^ 2
    if (i == nrow(df.filtered.2)) {
      LOOCV_MSE <- mean(error)
    }
  }
}
